"'''The Serpent Masters'''" is a [[Star Wars (comic strip)|comic strip]] written by [[Archie Goodwin]] and illustrated by [[Al Williamson]], originally published in [[1981]] by the [[Los Angeles Times Syndicate]]. It was later reprinted in ''[[Amazing Heroes]]'' magazine #13&ndash;16.

It was republished by [[Dark Horse Comics]], beginning on page 12 of [[Classic Star Wars 4|''Classic Star Wars'' 4]], all through [[Classic Star Wars 5|''Classic Star Wars'' 5]], and ending on page 6 of [[Classic Star Wars 6|''Classic Star Wars'' 6]]. It was again republished on [[StarWars.com]]'s webstrips section of [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
After his [[Mission to Fondor (Galactic Civil War)|Mission to Fondor]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] escaped from [[Fondor/Legends|Fondor]] with [[Tanith Shire]], who conducted him to [[Ophideraan]], the planet where the young girl's father was [[Slavery/Legends|enslaved]] by the [[Serpent Masters]]. They crashed on the planet, and Luke was also enslaved. He eventually defeated the Serpent Masters by duplicating the signal that controlled the [[flying serpent]]s and by inadvertently enticing [[Supreme Serpent Master|Supreme Master]] [[Tyrann]] to leap to his death.

